1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:03,360
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:18,080 --> 00:00:19,720
Thank you, Duang, for being by my side.

3
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,280
From now on,

4
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:23,240
just focus on becoming our boy again.

5
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:25,280
But I thank you

6
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:27,640
for being in his life.

7
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,040
I didn't choose him.

8
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:31,360
He chose me.

9
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:34,640
I'm not falling in love.

10
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:35,880
Marvis…

11
00:00:37,360 --> 00:00:38,400
Let's shower together.

12
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:40,280
<i>Save the planet.</i>

13
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,200
If I shower with you,
then we're going straight to sleep.

14
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,440
You got it.

15
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:05,600
I'm so happy to have you by my side.

16
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:08,840
Are you at ease now that everything
is over?

17
00:01:09,880 --> 00:01:11,760
I think everything that happened

18
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:13,880
has made me grow so much.

19
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:17,080
Besides,

20
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:19,600
your family is very cute.

21
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:25,040
So… Who's the cutest?

22
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,120
Duang.

23
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,720
Then,

24
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,320
for break,

25
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:37,760
do you want to go somewhere
with this cutie?

26
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:43,800
How about Japan?

27
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:45,000
Fukuoka.

28
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,440
Yes, yes, yes.

29
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,520
Let's go to Japan.

30
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:50,440
I'll go ahead and book the plane tickets.

31
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:52,360
I'll find us a hotel.

32
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:57,640
A nice change of scenery.

33
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:00,400
Before going to Fukuoka,

34
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,160
get your ass to class.

35
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,240
We still have to change.

36
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,640
Chop-chop.

37
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,960
You all right, little boy?

38
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,200
I'm sleepy.

39
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:01,640
Wanna lie down on me?

40
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:04,000
It's fine.

41
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,880
Even though it's a little confusing
that we're in Japan,

42
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:10,400
I think the timing is just perfect.

43
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,120
What do you mean?

44
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:17,160
Perfect for our honeymoon, of course.

45
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,920
Blushing, huh?

46
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:28,640
Don't think I'll let you off so easily.

47
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,040
What a big mouth.

48
00:04:30,120 --> 00:04:30,960
Stop it.

49
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,200
All right,

50
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:36,120
whatever you want, baby.

51
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,640
I'll move you to the back seat.

52
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,840
I don't want to.

53
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,520
I'm fine right here.

54
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:45,080
No way.

55
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,440
You're gonna be uncomfortable.

56
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,120
Come on.

57
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:53,800
One, two, three.

58
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:58,240
Watch your head.

59
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:08,040
Get in.

60
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:36,280
I'm not gonna be able to handle this…

61
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,600
Bear with me.

62
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:54,240
This is heavenly.
The ice cream doesn't even melt.

63
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,760
Can I have two more?

64
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,080
What?

65
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,920
What?!

66
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,040
Nothing, just…

67
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:12,360
<i>My baby is so cute</i>

68
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:15,280
<i>My heart will burst at the seams</i>

69
00:06:15,360 --> 00:06:18,280
<i>If they call me lovesick</i>

70
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:21,200
<i>I'd be cool with it</i>

71
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,720
You know that song too?

72
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:28,160
You don't normally
listen to that kind of music.

73
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:30,480
You're making me blush.

74
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,600
I wanna be into things you like too.

75
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:39,080
I'm blushing even harder!

76
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,160
Hey.

77
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,240
Today is our monthiversary again.

78
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,400
I want this trip to be a gift for you.

79
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,800
No,

80
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:57,360
it's too expensive.

81
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,120
No, no, not like that!

82
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,400
I misspoke.

83
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:03,520
I'm not saying that
I'm gonna pay for your whole trip,

84
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:06,800
but I have pocket money for your desserts.

85
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:09,000
I can pay for those,

86
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:10,000
so please let me.

87
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,840
If that's all, it's fine.

88
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:17,080
Because there's something
I want you to spoil me with.

89
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:19,760
Spoil you?

90
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:21,600
What's your request?

91
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:24,960
I want…

92
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,680
It's gonna be nasty, isn't it?

93
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,840
No, it's not.

94
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:32,800
I wanna ask you to use the same tone

95
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:35,040
I use to talk to you.

96
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:47,800
Can I pwease hear to it now?

97
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:48,800
No.

98
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,880
Pwease!

99
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,600
No.

100
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,440
Hey!

101
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:14,000
Should we go back to our room now?

102
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,880
Let's go back now.

103
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:25,200
You're such a flirt,

104
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,440
but I can handle it.

105
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,480
It was cold outside today,

106
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:03,200
so your skin is probably dry.

107
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,280
I got you this.

108
00:10:06,560 --> 00:10:08,080
Clear Nose Moisturizing Gel.

109
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,400
Let me put it on for you.

110
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,000
Your cheeks are so soft now!

111
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:53,720
- Ouch!
- Yours aren't.

112
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:55,800
Let me apply it.

113
00:11:22,760 --> 00:11:23,840
Are they soft now?

114
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:25,680
They are.

115
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,200
Then…

116
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:29,640
Should we continue over there?

117
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,680
I'll love you so hard.

118
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:36,640
No,

119
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,200
I'm sleepy.

120
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,560
Then I'll carry you.

121
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,520
What a bummer.

122
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,040
One day,

123
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:04,880
my time will come.

124
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,160
It's a shame

125
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,120
the weather isn't nice today.

126
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,360
It's fine.

127
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,280
As long as I'm with you,

128
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:19,560
anywhere is nice.

129
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:25,120
You used that tone with me…

130
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:26,560
The same tone I use with you!

131
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,440
This is just too much.

132
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:31,720
Give me your cheek.

133
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,800
This is nice.

134
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,120
I like this kind of life,

135
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:24,760
one that's ordinary

136
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,080
and without any dreams.

137
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,760
Just keep on living,

138
00:13:30,840 --> 00:13:32,720
enjoying the day,
and living in the moment.

139
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,880
If I were to die tomorrow,

140
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,640
I wouldn't feel incomplete.

141
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:41,920
How so?

142
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:43,920
Well…

143
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,200
I don't know if you realize

144
00:13:49,280 --> 00:13:51,600
that those ordinary days of mine

145
00:13:52,320 --> 00:13:53,560
are special because of you.

146
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,560
And it's also you

147
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,840
who makes me want to be
a better person every day.

148
00:13:59,920 --> 00:14:01,000
When I look at you,

149
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:03,480
I feel like

150
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:06,720
you were born with a cheat code.

151
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:09,280
Flawless and perfect.

152
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:11,040
No.

153
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,480
I'm not all that good.

154
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:18,280
I just have a habit of pressuring myself.

155
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,480
If there are 100 points,

156
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:23,840
I'll push for the full 100.

157
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,960
Sometimes, I think to myself

158
00:14:28,480 --> 00:14:30,320
it's better to get 101,

159
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,240
even though it's out of 100.

160
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,360
I just feel…

161
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,440
that I could do better.

162
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:43,120
Have I ever told you seriously

163
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,400
that my dream

164
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,600
is to succeed in jazz.

165
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:52,520
Isn't your dream to be a singer?

166
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,520
Yeah.

167
00:14:54,600 --> 00:14:57,560
I didn't realize until recently
that I like singing.

168
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:00,960
But I don't like being
in front of the camera.

169
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Maybe I could be…

170
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,440
a producer

171
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,280
working behind the scenes

172
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,760
or something along those lines.

173
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,760
Okay.

174
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:13,040
Then I'll live my life as an ordinary guy

175
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,920
who supports your dreams.

176
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:20,240
Do you really not have any dreams, Duang?

177
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:22,600
As your boyfriend,

178
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,520
I want to support you too.

179
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:31,360
If a dream is
something you wish for in the future,

180
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,840
my dream has been you.

181
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:41,720
And it's still about you.

182
00:15:42,920 --> 00:15:44,280
You're something else, Duang.

183
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,440
Come on, I'm serious.

184
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:53,320
I'm not sure.

185
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:57,320
I know that I like drawing,

186
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,520
and I'm pretty good at it.

187
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:03,520
I'm not praising myself, but many people
have complimented me.

188
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:07,400
I think I'll pursue drawing.

189
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,800
Drawing comics,

190
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,800
I kinda like it,

191
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:16,000
but will it be fun to read?

192
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:18,840
Maybe I could design game characters.

193
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,760
That's pretty interesting, I think.

194
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,320
If it is, give it a try.

195
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,360
But is this actually a dream?

196
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,400
I don't have a goal
I need to achieve or any of that.

197
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,080
It's fine.

198
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,880
You'll figure it out,

199
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:36,760
and I…

200
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:39,400
will be here to support you.

201
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,640
Right, speaking of which,

202
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:48,360
you might find something
you want to study here.

203
00:16:49,440 --> 00:16:50,520
Here?

204
00:16:51,360 --> 00:16:52,560
Japan, I mean.

205
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,680
Right,

206
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:56,080
I know about that.

207
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:58,080
I heard the students talking about it.

208
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,600
I'll look into it.

209
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,640
I'm sorry I'm not as cool as other people.

210
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,480
I like how cute you are.

211
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:18,000
I'm so lucky to have found you.

212
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,880
Wear this, baby.

213
00:19:31,960 --> 00:19:33,880
No, I like being cold.

214
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:41,560
Fine, I'll wear it.

215
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:46,360
Yay! You're the cutest.

216
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,360
Do you know

217
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:53,760
that if you get sick,

218
00:19:53,840 --> 00:19:56,600
you and I
will miss out on our travel plans?

219
00:19:56,680 --> 00:20:00,080
And that includes
the tea house you want to go to.

220
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,600
Let me check

221
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,960
if you're burning up.

222
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,560
Not at all.

223
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:18,120
I'll have to check somewhere else.

224
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,200
You!

225
00:20:30,640 --> 00:20:32,560
- Let's go.
- Hey, let's take a picture first.

226
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:34,320
Where?

227
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,800
Right here.

228
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:38,200
One, two, three.

229
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:43,040
What?

230
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:47,240
We can't take any more photos.
The film ran out.

231
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,160
That's a bummer.

232
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,600
I forgot to bring more rolls.

233
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:55,000
I brought some.

234
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,440
Whoa!

235
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,680
You brought some for me?

236
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,520
I knew you'd take a ton of photos.

237
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,040
Come on.

238
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,640
May I join you for tea?

239
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,680
Please do.

240
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:05,720
It's been such an honor.
Thank you for coming today.

241
00:22:29,520 --> 00:22:32,040
Bathing in warm water
when it's cold outside

242
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,320
feels so relaxing.

243
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:50,240
Right,

244
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,320
about when we got a tattoo together,

245
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:58,280
why did you choose the moon and the beach?

246
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:04,640
The moon doesn't suit you.

247
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:08,400
For me,

248
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,640
you're the sun.

249
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:48,160
What's up, bro?

250
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:51,320
<i>Hello?</i>

251
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:52,680
<i>I'm not gonna say a thing.</i>

252
00:23:54,040 --> 00:23:55,760
What the fuck is wrong with you, Jamie?

253
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,280
You're still there?

254
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:00,200
Honestly, what are you
doing there for a week?

255
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:02,880
<i>Right. So when are you coming back?</i>

256
00:24:02,960 --> 00:24:05,120
When you have your own lover.

257
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,320
<i>Bullshit.</i>

258
00:24:07,400 --> 00:24:10,000
You might as well relocate there

259
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:12,840
since you'll never
get to step foot in Nakhon Pathom again.

260
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,680
<i>- I'm a warrior,</i>
- "I'm a warrior…

261
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:17,520
<i>- not a lover…</i>
- …not a lover!"

262
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:20,360
How did you know
I was gonna say that?

263
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:22,160
<i>Who wouldn't? You always say that.</i>

264
00:24:22,240 --> 00:24:24,680
Yeah, even Tong and Kim know.

265
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:26,760
<i>Qin!</i>

266
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:29,280
<i>Duang, let me talk to Qin first.</i>

267
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:31,640
Not a chance.

268
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,200
Give it to me.

269
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,440
What is it, Jamie?

270
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:39,680
Qin, I miss you so much!

271
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:40,800
<i>Where are you?</i>

272
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,880
Bangkok or Nakhon Pathom?

273
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:45,080
In your heart.

274
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:48,600
<i>How has it been, Qin?</i>

275
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,960
Are you having fun?

276
00:24:50,040 --> 00:24:51,440
Is Duang taking good care of you?

277
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:52,600
It's fun.

278
00:24:52,680 --> 00:24:53,640
I'm pretty happy.

279
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:57,640
Are you calling because you're not happy?

280
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,360
Jeez!

281
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:01,160
You read me like a book.

282
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:04,760
<i>Qin.</i>

283
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,640
What's up?

284
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:10,160
What's the difference between
being into someone and liking them?

285
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,920
Liking someone…

286
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:18,280
means you're okay
with being with them or not.

287
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,760
Maybe you feel a little bummed,

288
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,480
but you're not that sad

289
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:25,680
<i>since there are</i>
<i>lots of many people to like.</i>

290
00:25:27,520 --> 00:25:28,640
Being into someone

291
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:31,720
is more specific.

292
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:35,200
If you don't have them,
you'll be in tears.

293
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:38,280
But if you love them,

294
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:42,760
it doesn't matter if you have them or not.

295
00:25:44,160 --> 00:25:45,760
<i>You just wanna be there</i>

296
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,360
<i>to see their face every day,</i>

297
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,160
<i>to feel, and to give,</i>

298
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:52,400
<i>even when you might get nothing in return.</i>

299
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:56,560
Anything else, Jamie?

300
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:58,920
<i>That's everything, Qin.</i>

301
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:01,240
<i>I'll hang up now. I've got my answer.</i>

302
00:26:01,320 --> 00:26:02,240
Bye.

303
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,680
Jamie.

304
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,760
Is he going to become a lover boy?

305
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,520
Maybe.

306
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:27,120
But I've always been a lover boy.

307
00:26:27,920 --> 00:26:29,120
You already know that.

308
00:26:30,600 --> 00:26:32,960
Then would you love me hard tonight?

309
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:49,040
Are you ready for me?

310
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:27,520
Here come the Japanese snacks!

311
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,680
- Whoa!
- Hey!

312
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:34,080
Hey!

313
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,760
Whoa!

314
00:32:38,120 --> 00:32:40,560
Three, two, one, go!

315
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:44,480
Don't be so possessive, Prachai!

316
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:46,000
Look in the mirror, Jettana!

317
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:48,360
- Give me that!
- Hey!

318
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,920
Can't you just share?

319
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:51,080
You fight like babies.

320
00:32:59,240 --> 00:33:01,480
Right, Duang, while you were gone,

321
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:04,480
this bastard disappeared
to who-knows-where for five days.

322
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:07,720
He even refused to tell me where!

323
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,840
Something is definitely up.

324
00:33:10,960 --> 00:33:11,800
What?!

325
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:14,720
Just a warrior
going into battle, like always.

326
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:15,880
Listen up.

327
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:18,440
If this warrior ever turns to a lover boy,
you can smack me.

328
00:33:18,520 --> 00:33:21,000
- I'm with Pae.
- What?! Duang!

329
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:25,800
So how was Japan?

330
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,080
As expected,

331
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:31,080
it's was our honeymoon.
Of course it was marvelous!

332
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,440
Stop flexing, would you?

333
00:33:34,480 --> 00:33:36,800
Well. aren't you the sore loser?

334
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:41,320
- Hey!
- I'll devour this whole damn thing!

335
00:33:42,880 --> 00:33:44,360
- Whoa!
- Let go!

336
00:33:45,840 --> 00:33:47,040
Let go of me!

337
00:33:49,440 --> 00:33:50,280
Hey! Time out.

338
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,240
Qin texted. Qin texted me.

339
00:34:05,080 --> 00:34:06,160
<i>When does your class end?</i>

340
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:09,719
<i>At 4:00 p.m. I'll rush over.</i>

341
00:34:13,840 --> 00:34:14,880
<i>Call me when your done.</i>

342
00:34:18,199 --> 00:34:19,040
What?!

343
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,600
Bro, wait! I haven't shown this one off!

344
00:34:33,600 --> 00:34:34,560
Excuse me.

345
00:34:39,199 --> 00:34:41,600
Can I sing for this year's Freshy Night?

346
00:34:41,679 --> 00:34:43,239
That's a good idea.

347
00:34:43,320 --> 00:34:45,600
What are you gonna play? Jazz?

348
00:34:47,520 --> 00:34:49,840
I wanna sing the song I wrote for Duang.

349
00:34:50,840 --> 00:34:52,600
Qin!

350
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:54,239
That's so sweet.

351
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:55,560
I'm looking forward to it.

352
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,000
Then, please excuse me.

353
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,000
Right, guys.

354
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:05,960
Thank you…

355
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,960
for letting me sing onstage last year.

356
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:28,600
<i>Are you done with class?</i>

357
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:29,560
<i>Hurry back.</i>

358
00:35:30,120 --> 00:35:31,480
<i>I'm getting lonely.</i>

359
00:35:31,560 --> 00:35:34,040
You can be so cute when you're fussy,

360
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,560
my Qin.

361
00:35:36,960 --> 00:35:37,840
<i>Hurry up.</i>

362
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:39,120
<i>I've got a surprise for you.</i>

363
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:41,200
Surprise…

364
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:42,720
What surprise, baby?

365
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:46,440
<i>How is it a surprise if I tell you?</i>

366
00:35:46,520 --> 00:35:49,160
<i>Hurry back and drive safely.</i>

367
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:50,280
All right.

368
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:55,960
I've gotta go.

369
00:35:56,040 --> 00:35:58,240
Off to Qin again, huh?

370
00:35:58,320 --> 00:36:00,080
Do I still have to say it?

371
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:01,560
I'm a lover boy.

372
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:03,160
I'm off.

373
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,440
- Yeah, me too.
- What?

374
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:10,360
Where are you going?

375
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:12,160
Not the same way he's going.

376
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,560
- Bye.
- What?

377
00:36:17,920 --> 00:36:19,680
I don't think
his lover boy era is far off.

378
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:26,920
I'm back!

379
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:32,160
Say hi to Uncle.

380
00:36:34,040 --> 00:36:34,960
You!

381
00:36:35,040 --> 00:36:37,800
Don't be so loud. You're gonna scare her.

382
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:41,640
Look.

383
00:36:47,400 --> 00:36:49,640
I'm gonna cry…

384
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:52,680
Isn't she cute?

385
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,640
Absolutely.

386
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,800
Good.

387
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:00,920
Uncle is a good guy, see?

388
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:18,480
What made you decide to buy her?

389
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:19,400
Yesterday,

390
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,680
I sent a friend to a corgi farm,

391
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:24,080
and they sent me a video.

392
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:26,280
I just had a feeling about her.

393
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:30,080
Tell me, how much was she?

394
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:31,960
Seven…

395
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:33,840
She was 7,000?!

396
00:37:33,920 --> 00:37:35,720
How about 70,000?

397
00:37:37,480 --> 00:37:39,840
Did you say 70,000?

398
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,440
The reason I picked her
is because she doesn't bark at all.

399
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:48,080
Also, she makes funny faces,
so I decided on her.

400
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,000
She's just like me.

401
00:37:50,840 --> 00:37:52,160
You…

402
00:37:52,240 --> 00:37:53,920
You're melting me.

403
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:59,200
Why do you have to be so gentle
and such an animal lover?

404
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:01,760
I'm head over heels in love with you.

405
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,240
Really now, Uncle?

406
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:09,080
But she was still 70,000 baht.

407
00:38:09,160 --> 00:38:11,680
I know you're rich,

408
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:14,000
but you still have to save up.

409
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:16,080
A purchase like this

410
00:38:16,840 --> 00:38:18,560
would give me a heart attack.

411
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:20,440
What money will I have to spoil you with?

412
00:38:22,160 --> 00:38:23,400
I don't want you to spoil me.

413
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:31,960
Qin?

414
00:38:32,720 --> 00:38:34,160
What is her name?

415
00:38:37,640 --> 00:38:39,280
I haven't come up with one.

416
00:38:40,280 --> 00:38:41,960
What should we name you, sweetie?

417
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:43,440
Why are you so fluffy?

418
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,440
How about Fluffy?

419
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:49,600
Whoa!

420
00:38:49,680 --> 00:38:50,800
Are you sure?

421
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:54,960
Well, she's cute and fluffy.

422
00:38:56,360 --> 00:38:57,400
Whoa!

423
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:00,320
Hey, she barked!

424
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:03,440
Is that your name, sweetie?

425
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,840
You're the cutest.

426
00:39:12,640 --> 00:39:15,880
Wait, if I'm Uncle,

427
00:39:17,520 --> 00:39:18,600
what are you?

428
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:20,320
I'm Papa, of course.

429
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:22,640
What? But I'm your boyfriend.

430
00:39:22,720 --> 00:39:23,640
So Uncle it is.

431
00:39:23,720 --> 00:39:25,520
But I wanna be Papa!

432
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:27,160
Then,

433
00:39:27,240 --> 00:39:30,320
you'll have to take Fluffy
to get vaccinated

434
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:34,440
and take her
for walks when I don't have time.

435
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:38,640
So that's all it takes to be here Papa?

436
00:39:39,960 --> 00:39:41,880
"Love me tons too."

437
00:39:48,120 --> 00:39:49,760
So small,

438
00:39:49,840 --> 00:39:51,400
yet already a papa.

439
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,720
I'm as big as you are.

440
00:39:55,520 --> 00:39:57,720
You're giving me cute aggression.

441
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:01,000
Who in the world
could be even cuter than a puppy?

442
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:02,840
Get your face off of me.

443
00:40:04,480 --> 00:40:05,480
I'm with my daughter.

444
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,960
She got you so hooked.

445
00:40:12,040 --> 00:40:13,680
I guess I'm not important anymore?

446
00:40:13,760 --> 00:40:15,200
Delusional.

447
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:16,840
She's ours, you know?

448
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:21,120
You're the cutest.

449
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,800
You really are cute.

450
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:29,800
Right, Duang.

451
00:40:29,880 --> 00:40:32,160
Give me a hand here.

452
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:37,200
How do you set this up?

453
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:51,480
Boo!

454
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:57,320
- Get in your house first.
- Here, this is how it's done.

455
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:24,800
Hey!

456
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,480
Come to bed.

457
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:37,400
Duang.

458
00:41:39,640 --> 00:41:42,000
Let's have Fluffy sleep with us.

459
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:45,200
Please, please, please.

460
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,840
No can do.

461
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:52,920
We need to train her to sleep in her bed!

462
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,440
We agreed on that, didn't we?

463
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:20,400
Please…

464
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:27,520
Don't pull that one on me.

465
00:42:27,600 --> 00:42:29,400
I won't look at you!

466
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:34,040
Are you jealous of our child?

467
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:36,280
If she sleeps in this bed,

468
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:37,920
you won't cuddle with me!

469
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:39,400
You're jealous.

470
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,240
Sure!

471
00:43:02,280 --> 00:43:03,680
You're possessive of me,

472
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:05,520
I'm also possessive of you.

473
00:43:12,360 --> 00:43:14,160
You said I was the only one for you,

474
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,840
and you're also the only one for me.

475
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:19,280
If I don't cuddle with you,

476
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:21,200
who would I cuddle with?

477
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:26,080
If you keep this up,

478
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:28,840
I'll get up and kiss you,

479
00:43:29,680 --> 00:43:31,800
and you won't get to go anywhere.

480
00:43:32,480 --> 00:43:33,960
This is final.

481
00:43:36,480 --> 00:43:38,160
You think I'm scared?

482
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:47,760
Fluffy!

483
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,240
What?

484
00:43:50,320 --> 00:43:51,160
Qin.

485
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:07,320
How nice that
we get to be with each other.

486
00:44:10,640 --> 00:44:12,840
What's really
on your mind when you say that?

487
00:44:16,440 --> 00:44:17,440
Do you know?

488
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:20,840
This time last year,

489
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:23,400
I couldn't sleep at all.

490
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:27,920
Just thinking that I'd meet, talk to you,

491
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,440
and ask to be in your world,

492
00:44:33,840 --> 00:44:35,320
it all felt so difficult.

493
00:44:36,680 --> 00:44:38,120
I was only smol, you know.

494
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:44,840
I didn't know
if I'd have to drown my sorrows

495
00:44:45,800 --> 00:44:48,360
in beer every day if you rejected me.

496
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:51,360
Who told you to be that lovesick?

497
00:44:52,360 --> 00:44:53,240
Right?

498
00:44:54,640 --> 00:44:56,640
Only one look at you,
and my heart flew away.

499
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,440
But you do know

500
00:45:01,520 --> 00:45:03,120
that I noticed you first.

501
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:08,480
You can keep it to yourself.

502
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:10,280
Not me though.

503
00:45:17,800 --> 00:45:19,240
I love you, Qin.

504
00:45:22,440 --> 00:45:24,200
I love you

505
00:45:24,280 --> 00:45:25,240
very much.

506
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:31,960
I'll love you even more.

507
00:45:32,680 --> 00:45:33,640
Can I?

508
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:39,360
It's Loy Krathong tomorrow.

509
00:45:41,920 --> 00:45:43,120
Last year,

510
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:44,680
I asked to win your heart.

511
00:45:45,400 --> 00:45:46,400
This year

512
00:45:47,720 --> 00:45:50,000
can I float my krathong with you?

513
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:54,800
I'll let you do it with me every year.

514
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:56,040
How does that sound?

515
00:45:56,720 --> 00:45:57,840
I'm down.

516
00:45:58,640 --> 00:45:59,720
Every year, right?

517
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:05,400
Your class is about to start.

518
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:07,360
Stay focused in class.

519
00:46:10,240 --> 00:46:11,800
Qin!

520
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:13,800
I miss you so much…

521
00:46:14,400 --> 00:46:15,960
Go away! Shoo!

522
00:46:17,080 --> 00:46:18,320
You're getting him all dirty.

523
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:20,240
Are you all right?

524
00:46:20,320 --> 00:46:21,960
Did he get you dirty?

525
00:46:22,040 --> 00:46:25,360
Jeez. Damn you, Cheewin!

526
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:27,600
I'm a person, not some germs!

527
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:32,760
You're being too much, Jamie.
They're boyfriends.

528
00:46:32,840 --> 00:46:34,760
Yeah, you don't know any better!

529
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:44,120
Hey.

530
00:46:48,680 --> 00:46:51,240
Right, I just realized
that today is Loy Krathong

531
00:46:51,320 --> 00:46:53,240
when I saw students
setting up food stalls.

532
00:46:53,320 --> 00:46:55,600
This year, Loy Krathong
is before Freshy Night.

533
00:46:55,680 --> 00:46:58,360
- How could you not know what today is?
- What?

534
00:46:58,440 --> 00:47:01,520
Right, are you
gonna go float krathongs tonight?

535
00:47:01,600 --> 00:47:03,080
Let me come with you.

536
00:47:03,160 --> 00:47:05,880
Damn, no one
asked me to the festival this year.

537
00:47:09,960 --> 00:47:11,000
Come with us.

538
00:47:11,800 --> 00:47:13,040
I think I'll go with Qin,

539
00:47:13,120 --> 00:47:14,480
and these two will come with us.

540
00:47:17,800 --> 00:47:20,400
So, no girls have asked you this year?

541
00:47:20,480 --> 00:47:21,840
No.

542
00:47:21,920 --> 00:47:23,280
But there was, last year.

543
00:47:24,360 --> 00:47:27,120
A girl invited me
to float a krathong with her.

544
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:33,480
So what was her name? Was it Cherry?

545
00:47:33,560 --> 00:47:35,000
Yes.

546
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:37,800
Wait, how did you know?

547
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:48,680
I am Cherry.

548
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:50,400
<i>I am Cherry…</i>

549
00:47:50,480 --> 00:47:52,080
<i>I am Cherry…</i>

550
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:54,960
<i>I am Cherry…</i>

551
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:13,000
- Sorry, bro.
- Sorry, bro.

552
00:48:15,320 --> 00:48:16,960
You bastards!

553
00:48:18,120 --> 00:48:20,800
I'll beat you guys like a drum.

554
00:48:20,880 --> 00:48:22,480
Bastards, come here!

555
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:23,720
Hey!

556
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:24,800
Pae!

557
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:28,920
No, no, no, don't hit me!

558
00:48:33,600 --> 00:48:35,000
Hey, hey, Jamie!

559
00:48:35,080 --> 00:48:37,840
- Help me!
- Hey! It's Duang!

560
00:48:37,920 --> 00:48:40,000
Over there! Go!

561
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:42,240
I'm not going with you anymore, bastards.

562
00:48:58,280 --> 00:49:01,080
Baby.

563
00:49:01,160 --> 00:49:02,920
It's the Loy Krathong festival.

564
00:49:05,560 --> 00:49:08,560
- These two are so lovely-dovey.
- True.

565
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:11,000
The pond is turning into sweet syrup now.

566
00:49:11,080 --> 00:49:14,160
I can't believe that Qin has a boyfriend.

567
00:49:14,240 --> 00:49:15,160
Right.

568
00:49:15,240 --> 00:49:16,560
They even have a child now,

569
00:49:16,640 --> 00:49:19,320
even though it's a corgi.

570
00:49:20,800 --> 00:49:22,600
Right, so where is Tong?

571
00:49:22,680 --> 00:49:25,680
Man, he got so sulky and went home.

572
00:49:26,360 --> 00:49:28,680
Jeez, that's all right.
I'll make it up to him.

573
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:29,720
Hey,

574
00:49:31,520 --> 00:49:34,560
I'm so happy that I finally get to
float my krathong with you.

575
00:49:35,840 --> 00:49:37,440
I'm blushing now.

576
00:49:38,920 --> 00:49:40,360
"I'll finally get to float…"

577
00:49:40,440 --> 00:49:41,720
You always blush.

578
00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:44,520
Get used to having me by your side.

579
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,920
Whoa, I could literally die…

580
00:49:49,720 --> 00:49:53,360
Okay, I'll spend forever with you.

581
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:00,280
Not today.

582
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:02,560
- Let's go.
- Absolutely not.

583
00:50:02,640 --> 00:50:04,120
Gosh, Pae.

584
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:05,400
My bestie.

585
00:51:01,080 --> 00:51:02,600
There's something I wanna give you.

586
00:51:05,720 --> 00:51:06,560
What is it?

587
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:14,320
DUANG WITH YOU

588
00:51:14,400 --> 00:51:15,520
This is Duang,

589
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:16,760
and this is you.

590
00:51:18,240 --> 00:51:20,040
"Duang with you."

591
00:51:22,480 --> 00:51:24,360
Here, take a look.

592
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:34,640
"Hey, my buddy likes you."

593
00:51:36,440 --> 00:51:37,520
My name is "Buddy."

594
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:48,520
"Can I walk you home?"

595
00:51:58,200 --> 00:51:59,640
This one,

596
00:51:59,720 --> 00:52:03,040
I didn't say anything, just following you.

597
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:11,000
This is when I liked watching you eat

598
00:52:11,080 --> 00:52:12,600
so I could get your order right.

599
00:52:22,120 --> 00:52:24,080
If I don't ask you now,

600
00:52:24,920 --> 00:52:26,600
I'll probably go insane.

601
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:30,920
"Will you be my boyfriend?"

602
00:52:33,600 --> 00:52:35,120
You!

603
00:52:35,760 --> 00:52:36,600
Will you?

604
00:52:36,680 --> 00:52:38,920
Wait, we already are.

605
00:52:47,640 --> 00:52:49,280
This is your monthiversary gift.

606
00:52:50,240 --> 00:52:53,680
There are still so many pictures inside,
be sure to look at them.

607
00:52:55,320 --> 00:52:56,360
It must've taken ages.

608
00:52:57,520 --> 00:52:58,960
Well, the entire year.

609
00:52:59,040 --> 00:53:00,120
Do you like it?

610
00:53:02,320 --> 00:53:04,760
Thank you
for putting so much thought into it.

611
00:53:04,840 --> 00:53:07,320
Can you do it
for this year's Freshy Night too?

612
00:53:07,400 --> 00:53:08,720
I'll be onstage.

613
00:53:10,960 --> 00:53:12,280
Totally!

614
00:53:12,360 --> 00:53:15,840
I'll be cheering you front and center!

615
00:53:18,400 --> 00:53:21,880
I'm looking forward to it.
I have a gift prepared for you too.

616
00:53:23,920 --> 00:53:25,000
A gift?

617
00:53:25,960 --> 00:53:27,960
What gift?

618
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:29,600
I wanna know!

619
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:31,360
I'm not telling you.

620
00:53:34,600 --> 00:53:35,920
Wait.

621
00:53:41,400 --> 00:53:42,920
How freaking cute.

622
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:48,960
Come on, guys.

623
00:53:49,040 --> 00:53:50,120
Cheers.

624
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:51,520
It's my treat today.

625
00:53:51,600 --> 00:53:55,640
Let's celebrate Duang
having a boyfriend! Cheers!

626
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:58,360
- I want me a lover too!
- Wow…

627
00:53:58,480 --> 00:53:59,680
- Bottoms up.
- Thank you, bro.

628
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:00,840
Anytime.

629
00:54:00,920 --> 00:54:04,000
- This Nakhon Pathom lover boy is my pal.
- Wow, that's wicked.

630
00:54:05,560 --> 00:54:07,200
Drink up. Fill it to the brim.

631
00:54:10,120 --> 00:54:11,160
Don't hold back.

632
00:54:11,240 --> 00:54:12,480
I'm already feeling it.

633
00:54:25,040 --> 00:54:26,440
Hey, Qin.

634
00:54:28,040 --> 00:54:29,400
Duang.

635
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:43,680
Wanna go say hi to them?

636
00:54:45,840 --> 00:54:46,840
No.

637
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:47,880
I'll use the restroom.

638
00:54:57,760 --> 00:54:58,920
I'm sorry!

639
00:55:01,160 --> 00:55:03,760
Ma'am, please don't do this.
My boyfriend won't like it.

640
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:06,080
I'm too wasted. I can't…

641
00:55:07,200 --> 00:55:08,040
Sorry…

642
00:55:17,760 --> 00:55:19,600
I'm sorry. I'm drunk.

643
00:55:24,240 --> 00:55:26,120
I don't know him. I don't.

644
00:55:33,440 --> 00:55:35,440
Can you not let anyone
get close like that again?

645
00:55:35,520 --> 00:55:38,120
I don't wanna come off as unlovely to you.

646
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:41,720
I'm sure you'll always be lovely.

647
00:55:41,800 --> 00:55:43,720
From the start

648
00:55:43,800 --> 00:55:46,440
until forever!

649
00:55:46,520 --> 00:55:49,080
Make sure it doesn't happen again.

650
00:55:49,160 --> 00:55:51,080
Your wish is my command!

651
00:55:51,640 --> 00:55:54,320
I'm not even sure
if I should be jealous or annoyed.

652
00:55:54,400 --> 00:55:56,760
These two are so adorable
that they don't even fight.

653
00:55:59,680 --> 00:56:00,760
- Let's cheers.
- Come on.

654
00:56:02,000 --> 00:56:02,840
That's true.

655
00:56:02,960 --> 00:56:04,240
You're jealous of them, huh?

656
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:06,040
Wanna go to the restroom?

657
00:56:06,120 --> 00:56:07,480
- Let's go.
- Come on.

658
00:56:07,560 --> 00:56:08,800
Well, well, well.

659
00:56:10,960 --> 00:56:12,520
- Excuse me.
- Please.

660
00:56:45,560 --> 00:56:47,040
Don't smile.

661
00:56:48,120 --> 00:56:51,000
So I can't even smile now? That's sad.

662
00:57:02,880 --> 00:57:03,960
It's good.

663
00:57:05,120 --> 00:57:06,040
Want a taste?

664
00:57:14,880 --> 00:57:16,160
Jettana.

665
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:21,640
What say you?

666
00:57:44,240 --> 00:57:45,520
"What say you"?

667
00:57:48,760 --> 00:57:50,000
My bad, my bad.

668
00:57:50,080 --> 00:57:51,840
I won't use complicated words anymore.

669
00:57:51,920 --> 00:57:55,560
It's how the Northerners say, "What's up?"

670
00:57:56,400 --> 00:57:57,400
Okay,

671
00:57:58,360 --> 00:57:59,720
what say you?

672
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:04,280
I say nothing.

673
00:58:04,360 --> 00:58:05,400
Please.

674
00:58:23,280 --> 00:58:25,680
After the laps, let's have guay jap yuan.

675
00:58:25,760 --> 00:58:28,960
I don't know what it is,
but I don't mind tagging along.

676
00:58:29,040 --> 00:58:31,160
Why did you say yes so easily?

677
00:58:33,760 --> 00:58:37,240
I'm not saying you're easy,
and I'd never think that way.

678
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:39,720
Maybe we're kindred spirits.

679
00:58:43,760 --> 00:58:46,520
Wow! You know such fancy words.

680
00:58:46,600 --> 00:58:47,480
Praise me.

681
00:58:49,680 --> 00:58:52,760
Amazing job, gorgeous little pookie.

682
00:58:54,400 --> 00:58:55,560
"Gorgeous little pookie"?

683
00:58:56,400 --> 00:58:57,720
It's like…

684
00:58:57,800 --> 00:59:00,000
a term to use with someone you adore.

685
00:59:00,080 --> 00:59:03,040
Normally, the word "gorgeous"
is traditionally used with girls, right?

686
00:59:03,120 --> 00:59:05,640
As far as I know.

687
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:08,920
Nowadays, it can be used
with anyone you adore,

688
00:59:09,000 --> 00:59:10,840
- like…
- Gorgeous Jamie?

689
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:19,560
Was I wrong?

690
00:59:19,640 --> 00:59:21,120
Do you wanna see tears?

691
00:59:22,840 --> 00:59:23,760
Whose tears?

692
00:59:25,200 --> 00:59:28,160
Let's keep running.
This conversation's making me wanna cry.

693
00:59:28,240 --> 00:59:29,520
Fine, I'm sorry.

694
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:32,080
Give me a kiss and I'll feel better.

695
00:59:45,920 --> 00:59:48,000
Don't you do that
with just anyone, got it?

696
00:59:54,760 --> 00:59:56,480
Liking means you're fine either way.

697
00:59:56,560 --> 00:59:59,160
You're probably bummed, but not regretful.
Lock that in, Jamie.

698
01:00:01,240 --> 01:00:02,600
Wait up!

699
01:00:08,360 --> 01:00:09,320
Feel like it now?

700
01:00:10,040 --> 01:00:12,200
Right here?

701
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:14,520
Are we talking about the same thing?

702
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:20,640
What did you say?

703
01:00:22,520 --> 01:00:23,840
What did you say to me?

704
01:00:27,480 --> 01:00:29,520
Get over here!

705
01:00:37,280 --> 01:00:38,440
Thank you.

706
01:00:39,880 --> 01:00:41,880
Jamie, are you holding up okay?

707
01:00:41,960 --> 01:00:44,080
That's so insulting!

708
01:00:45,000 --> 01:00:46,600
Well, you do look really tired.

709
01:00:47,600 --> 01:00:49,800
You're really good at running.

710
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:54,360
When I get stressed out,
I like working out.

711
01:00:54,440 --> 01:00:57,280
That run was a joke.

712
01:00:58,080 --> 01:00:59,800
"A joke."

713
01:01:01,320 --> 01:01:02,600
You just love to tease me.

714
01:01:18,640 --> 01:01:19,520
All done.

715
01:01:22,840 --> 01:01:24,760
Let's go eat
the thing you mentioned earlier.

716
01:01:27,640 --> 01:01:29,080
I'm so tired.

717
01:01:30,240 --> 01:01:33,560
Come on, Jettana. Hurry up, Jettana.

718
01:01:34,520 --> 01:01:35,520
Come here, Jettana!

719
01:01:37,040 --> 01:01:38,440
What is this about?

720
01:01:39,160 --> 01:01:40,120
What?

721
01:01:46,760 --> 01:01:48,320
YOU

722
01:02:23,200 --> 01:02:26,000
SAMPANTHASIL UNIVERSITY

723
01:02:29,920 --> 01:02:31,120
Right, guys.

724
01:02:31,200 --> 01:02:33,720
Earlier, I saw someone
drinking chrysanthemum tea.

725
01:02:33,800 --> 01:02:35,720
He was dressed so nicely.

726
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:38,440
I can back him up on that.

727
01:02:39,160 --> 01:02:42,080
He turned everyone's heads.
I'm so confused.

728
01:02:42,160 --> 01:02:45,000
Who is he? Is he even from planet Earth?

729
01:02:45,080 --> 01:02:47,560
It's better than you could imagine,

730
01:02:47,640 --> 01:02:49,680
maybe even beyond your wildest dreams.

731
01:02:49,760 --> 01:02:51,600
Maybe he's a tourist?

732
01:02:51,680 --> 01:02:54,200
In what fucking world does a tourist
just hang out at uni?

733
01:02:54,280 --> 01:02:55,200
Are you nuts?

734
01:02:56,240 --> 01:02:58,320
Is it someone who dresses stylishly?

735
01:02:59,320 --> 01:03:01,240
- Yeah.
- Bingo. That's the one.

736
01:03:03,800 --> 01:03:05,760
He's waiting at the wrong building.

737
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:09,840
- How would you know?
- Yeah.

738
01:03:29,960 --> 01:03:31,360
Jamie.

739
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:45,720
Let me introduce you to him.

740
01:03:45,800 --> 01:03:47,240
This is Marvis.

741
01:03:50,040 --> 01:03:51,840
Hello!

742
01:03:51,920 --> 01:03:53,360
This is Duang.

743
01:03:53,440 --> 01:03:54,680
He's Pae.

744
01:03:55,280 --> 01:03:56,560
That's Tong and Kim.

745
01:03:56,640 --> 01:03:58,840
And this is Qin,
the one I was telling you about.

746
01:04:00,720 --> 01:04:01,920
Hello.

747
01:04:02,000 --> 01:04:04,560
You can just call me Mar. I won't bite.

748
01:04:05,240 --> 01:04:08,880
Jamie, you're something else,
you know that?

749
01:04:08,960 --> 01:04:10,200
My heart was sinking there…

750
01:04:10,280 --> 01:04:12,840
Are you feeling sick? Are you okay?

751
01:04:14,360 --> 01:04:16,240
I am okay. I am.

752
01:04:16,320 --> 01:04:18,640
You really teased him there.

753
01:04:18,720 --> 01:04:20,960
That one's already so unique.

754
01:04:21,040 --> 01:04:23,280
I wasn't teasing him,

755
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,640
just simply saying hi.

756
01:04:27,320 --> 01:04:29,040
Want some snacks?

757
01:04:42,760 --> 01:04:44,720
Duang! Keep your boyfriend in check.

758
01:04:44,800 --> 01:04:46,680
Qin!

759
01:04:46,760 --> 01:04:48,120
Gosh…

760
01:04:48,200 --> 01:04:50,840
You didn't even blink
when you looked at him.

761
01:04:50,920 --> 01:04:52,200
I'm sulking now!

762
01:04:52,920 --> 01:04:54,240
What's with you?

763
01:04:56,640 --> 01:04:58,680
So… What's this?

764
01:04:58,760 --> 01:05:01,840
Yeah, are you making it official?

765
01:05:03,760 --> 01:05:05,800
I'm not spilling any beans to you, Duang.

766
01:05:06,560 --> 01:05:08,880
I don't wanna know at all. Right, Qin?

767
01:05:08,960 --> 01:05:11,280
I'll take you to get ready for your show.

768
01:05:11,360 --> 01:05:14,920
Wouldn't wanna be
around someone so full of secrets!

769
01:05:15,000 --> 01:05:17,160
Mar, you can come with. You're invited.

770
01:05:18,240 --> 01:05:21,360
I'll have to pass. I have
an online meeting with my professor.

771
01:05:21,440 --> 01:05:22,640
Jamie,

772
01:05:22,720 --> 01:05:24,640
go have fun with your friends.

773
01:05:25,760 --> 01:05:28,040
Jamie, are you his dog?

774
01:05:29,880 --> 01:05:31,320
Jeez…Duang.

775
01:05:31,400 --> 01:05:33,720
That's rich coming from you.

776
01:05:36,280 --> 01:05:38,680
Duang, my pal.

777
01:05:39,240 --> 01:05:41,760
Why are you whispering to him?

778
01:05:41,840 --> 01:05:44,040
No… I didn't say anything.

779
01:05:44,120 --> 01:05:46,360
I just said not to fall too hard in love,

780
01:05:46,880 --> 01:05:49,080
since you're a warrior, not a lover!

781
01:05:49,800 --> 01:05:50,840
Stupid Duang!

782
01:05:52,280 --> 01:05:54,280
Hey, let's go. Quick.

783
01:05:56,560 --> 01:05:57,920
Fine then!

784
01:05:58,000 --> 01:06:01,000
Warrior… Lover…

785
01:06:01,080 --> 01:06:02,880
Is that some kind of wordplay?

786
01:06:04,080 --> 01:06:09,840
Your broken Thai is the cutest!

787
01:06:12,120 --> 01:06:15,080
Has Jamie ever been like this before?

788
01:06:15,160 --> 01:06:19,440
Nope. I think
he's caught lover boy sickness from Duang.

789
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:23,000
Don't get too obsessed.

790
01:06:23,080 --> 01:06:26,120
You could end up
as another pup falling from a plane.

791
01:06:26,200 --> 01:06:27,960
- Mr. Prachai.
- Yes?

792
01:06:28,040 --> 01:06:29,600
Why are you talking to me like that?

793
01:06:29,680 --> 01:06:32,440
- Why act so tense?
- I'm not acting.

794
01:06:32,520 --> 01:06:33,480
This is natural.

795
01:06:33,560 --> 01:06:35,640
- There.
- My legs are pretty tensed up, I mean.

796
01:06:38,600 --> 01:06:40,520
Think it over, Marvis.

797
01:06:52,200 --> 01:06:53,160
Do I look good?

798
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:58,320
You do.

799
01:07:05,720 --> 01:07:08,080
You haven't put on any cologne though.

800
01:07:10,520 --> 01:07:11,560
How about this one?

801
01:07:12,520 --> 01:07:13,360
Sure.

802
01:07:19,120 --> 01:07:20,800
Nope.

803
01:07:22,800 --> 01:07:24,240
What about this one?

804
01:07:27,800 --> 01:07:30,680
Nope, let's do a different one.

805
01:07:31,960 --> 01:07:34,520
We should go with this one!

806
01:07:37,000 --> 01:07:37,880
Okay.

807
01:07:43,840 --> 01:07:46,600
- But I think we should try something…
- Duang.

808
01:07:48,440 --> 01:07:50,800
This one's fine. This will do, right?

809
01:08:08,600 --> 01:08:10,080
That smells heavenly.

810
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:18,200
Let's head out.

811
01:08:29,319 --> 01:08:32,840
All right, all right.

812
01:08:32,920 --> 01:08:35,160
Before moving on to the next performance,

813
01:08:35,240 --> 01:08:37,120
we have a very,

814
01:08:37,200 --> 01:08:38,680
very special show.

815
01:08:38,760 --> 01:08:40,800
That's right. He's a jazz sophomore

816
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:43,240
who will surprise us tonight.

817
01:08:43,319 --> 01:08:46,640
Yes, and I have to mention
that he's a person of few words,

818
01:08:46,720 --> 01:08:49,640
but tonight, he will use a song

819
01:08:49,720 --> 01:08:51,680
to express what he's feeling.

820
01:08:51,760 --> 01:08:54,200
He will warm your heart,
leave you impressed,

821
01:08:54,279 --> 01:08:57,240
and might even bring you to tears.

822
01:08:57,319 --> 01:08:59,040
Exactly. If you're ready,

823
01:08:59,120 --> 01:09:00,560
please give it up

824
01:09:00,640 --> 01:09:03,880
for Qin, a second-year jazz student!

825
01:09:23,960 --> 01:09:25,080
Last year,

826
01:09:27,040 --> 01:09:29,240
someone said

827
01:09:29,319 --> 01:09:31,399
that he was enchanted by my voice.

828
01:09:33,240 --> 01:09:34,240
This year…

829
01:09:35,279 --> 01:09:37,240
I have a song just for him.

830
01:09:37,359 --> 01:09:38,640
This is my monthiversary gift.

831
01:09:41,160 --> 01:09:44,080
May everyone
who has joined this university

832
01:09:44,160 --> 01:09:45,720
indulge in happiness,

833
01:09:47,160 --> 01:09:48,160
find good friends,

834
01:09:48,760 --> 01:09:50,399
and find a love that feels right.

835
01:09:53,240 --> 01:09:54,120
Duang,

836
01:09:56,360 --> 01:09:58,200
I wrote this song for you.

837
01:10:19,240 --> 01:10:22,000
<i>I have always been so numb</i>

838
01:10:22,080 --> 01:10:25,520
<i>To everything and everyone</i>

839
01:10:25,600 --> 01:10:31,320
<i>Like a heartless soul</i>

840
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:35,600
<i>Since I was always hurt from the start</i>

841
01:10:35,680 --> 01:10:39,280
<i>I kept the door shut and hid my heart</i>

842
01:10:39,360 --> 01:10:43,280
<i>Oh, how it became unfeeling</i>

843
01:10:43,360 --> 01:10:45,880
<i>With no way of healing</i>

844
01:10:45,960 --> 01:10:49,840
<i>But the world changed so suddenly</i>

845
01:10:49,920 --> 01:10:53,560
<i>As our eyes met, my baby</i>

846
01:10:53,640 --> 01:10:59,040
<i>Never once have I felt so strongly</i>

847
01:11:03,080 --> 01:11:04,080
<i>I will win your heart.</i>

848
01:11:04,880 --> 01:11:06,440
<i>Good luck with that then.</i>

849
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:10,960
<i>I'm thankful that you're right next to me</i>

850
01:11:11,040 --> 01:11:14,440
<i>I'm thankful there's us right where we are</i>

851
01:11:14,520 --> 01:11:18,800
<i>I'm thankful for the countless stars</i>

852
01:11:18,880 --> 01:11:21,680
<i>That made us cross paths so perfectly</i>

853
01:11:21,760 --> 01:11:24,600
<i>You are the very song</i>

854
01:11:24,680 --> 01:11:28,440
<i>I've always longed for</i>

855
01:11:28,520 --> 01:11:30,320
<i>I'm thankful that you've found me</i>

856
01:11:30,400 --> 01:11:34,080
<i>Reminding me so beautifully</i>

857
01:11:34,160 --> 01:11:37,440
<i>With you, I'm happy</i>

858
01:11:41,920 --> 01:11:45,640
<i>You've become my every breath</i>

859
01:11:45,720 --> 01:11:49,040
<i>Pushing me to go forward</i>

860
01:11:49,120 --> 01:11:52,560
<i>From now on, I won't ever be afraid</i>

861
01:11:52,640 --> 01:11:55,800
<i>As long as we embrace</i>

862
01:11:55,880 --> 01:11:59,320
<i>I've waited long for this day</i>

863
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:03,120
<i>The only answer I've ever wanted</i>

864
01:12:03,200 --> 01:12:05,360
<i>Is you</i>

865
01:12:06,240 --> 01:12:08,080
<i>Is you…</i>

866
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:44,360
<i>And the world changed so suddenly</i>

867
01:12:44,440 --> 01:12:47,720
<i>As our eyes met, my baby</i>

868
01:12:47,800 --> 01:12:50,680
<i>Never once</i>

869
01:12:50,760 --> 01:12:56,160
<i>Have I felt so strongly</i>

870
01:12:56,840 --> 01:13:00,720
<i>I'm thankful that you're right next to me</i>

871
01:13:00,800 --> 01:13:04,120
<i>From this moment till eternity</i>

872
01:13:04,200 --> 01:13:07,920
<i>I'm thankful for the countless stars</i>

873
01:13:08,000 --> 01:13:11,040
<i>That have drawn us to love so perfectly</i>

874
01:13:11,120 --> 01:13:13,680
<i>You are the very song</i>

875
01:13:14,360 --> 01:13:18,240
<i>I've always longed for</i>

876
01:13:18,320 --> 01:13:20,240
<i>I'm thankful that you've found me</i>

877
01:13:20,320 --> 01:13:23,720
<i>Reminding me of every moment I love you</i>

878
01:13:23,800 --> 01:13:28,440
<i>With you, I'm happy</i>

879
01:13:35,840 --> 01:13:42,480
<i>You are the heart I've always longed for</i>

880
01:13:58,720 --> 01:13:59,920
Don't cry just yet,

881
01:14:00,760 --> 01:14:02,040
not until I'm in front of you.

882
01:14:27,520 --> 01:14:28,520
Duang,

883
01:14:29,760 --> 01:14:31,200
I love you.

884
01:14:48,760 --> 01:14:50,400
I love you too.

885
01:14:55,600 --> 01:14:56,920
Are you ready?

886
01:14:57,000 --> 01:14:59,040
Are we ready for the next performance?

887
01:14:59,560 --> 01:15:00,480
Are we? Come on!

888
01:15:03,360 --> 01:15:04,640
Okay!

889
01:16:25,760 --> 01:16:27,640
Make some noise if you're happy!

890
01:16:27,720 --> 01:16:29,960
Raise your hands!

891
01:16:42,200 --> 01:16:43,160
Beautiful!

892
01:16:43,240 --> 01:16:44,840
Freshmen, sing along!

893
01:16:57,720 --> 01:16:58,560
Louder!

894
01:17:00,240 --> 01:17:01,120
Once more!

895
01:17:18,560 --> 01:17:20,760
Thank you, freshmen!

896
01:17:23,080 --> 01:17:24,440
Oh, where are you, Cinderella?

897
01:17:24,520 --> 01:17:26,680
Make some noise!

898
01:17:28,440 --> 01:17:29,280
Come on!

899
01:18:36,480 --> 01:18:39,120
All right, freshmen,
if you're still at it, make some noise!

900
01:20:08,360 --> 01:20:09,320
Duang.

901
01:20:11,880 --> 01:20:13,200
I'm hungry.

902
01:20:13,320 --> 01:20:14,400
Let's go eat.

903
01:20:18,120 --> 01:20:19,320
Let's go.

904
01:20:20,880 --> 01:20:22,000
<i>Between Qin and I,</i>

905
01:20:22,080 --> 01:20:23,880
<i>nothing has ever changed</i>

906
01:20:27,040 --> 01:20:30,760
<i>since I've already prepared</i>
<i>to love him with everything I have.</i>

907
01:20:30,840 --> 01:20:32,400
<i>Me too.</i>

908
01:21:07,280 --> 01:21:10,360
That's a wrap for <i>Duang with You!</i>

909
01:21:10,440 --> 01:21:13,720
Mommies!
